headline: HP Beats Expectations As AI PCs Grow And Cost Pressures Mount
summary: HP Inc (NYSE:HPQ) reported quarterly results that were ahead of market expectations, supported by strong AI PC shipments. The Personal Systems segment showed solid momentum as customers adopted AI-enabled PCs. Management highlighted rising DRAM and NAND memory costs as a key margin pressure. HP is pursuing long term supply agreements, product reconfiguration, pricing moves, and a $1b cost-saving plan targeted by FY2028. headline: Dell forecasts fiscal 2027 revenue above estimates on rising AI server demand
summary: Dell forecast fiscal 2027 revenue above Wall Street estimates on Thursday, betting on growing demand for its artificial ‌intelligence-optimized servers, sending its shares up around 11% in extended trading. The company ‌also announced a 20% hike in its cash dividend and an additional $10 billion for its share repurchase ​program. Big Tech firms, such as Alphabet, Microsoft, Amazon and Meta, are expected to spend at least $630 billion to build AI infrastructure this year, which would boost demand for vendors like Dell and rival Super Micro Computer.
